Japan's biggest construction company, Shimizu Corp.,  said Thursday its pre-tax earnings declined 10 percent from a year earlier to  120 billion yen (1.17 billion dollars) in the year to March.
The company said revenue dropped four percent to to 2.09 trillion yen and  forecast a sharply lower profit of 50 billion yen for the current year with  revenue sliding further to around 1.8 trillion yen.
